### While Loops

A **while loop** repeats code **as long as** a condition is true.

---

### While Loop

```js
let i = 1;
while (i <= 5) {
  console.log(i);
  i++;
}
```

The condition is checked **before** each iteration. If the condition starts as false, the loop never runs.

---

### Do/While Loop

The **do/while** loop runs **at least once** because the condition is checked after:

```js
let i = 1;
do {
  console.log(i);
  i++;
} while (i <= 5);
```

---

### While vs For

| Aspect | For Loop | While Loop |
|--------|----------|------------|
| **Best for** | Known number of iterations | Unknown number of iterations |
| **Example** | Loop through array | Read until data ends |
| **Risk** | Off-by-one | Infinite loop |

---

### Infinite Loops (Danger!)

Make sure the condition eventually becomes `false`:

```js
// DANGER: This never ends!
let i = 1;
while (i > 0) {
  console.log(i);
  i++; // i keeps growing, never becomes <= 0
}
```

> **Always** update your loop variable inside the loop to avoid infinite loops which crash your program.

codeExample:
let count = 1;
while (count <= 3) {
  console.log(`Count: ${count}`);
  count++;
}

let input = 0;
do {
  console.log(`Number: ${input}`);
  input++;
} while (input < 3);
